The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | International | Julia loved Indian food during Love shooting
                                                                                                                           17                                                                                      Julia loved Indian food during Love shooting
                              Amazingly spicy                            
	Los Angeles, Oct. 4 (PTI): India was her characters spiritual destination in Eat Pray Love.        
	However, actress Julia Roberts made the most of her shoot by gorging on local delicacies. The films Indian shoot concentrated on the spiritual path, but Roberts said she had gastronomical adventures too in India.        
	Roberts, 42, shot parts of the film, based on the memoirs of Elizabeth Gilbert, in an ashram and Pataudi Palace, Gurgaon, in September last year.         
	Its amazing how much Indian food you can eat in five weeks. Im pretty picky but I really like Indian food. Just every once in a while, you run into something that is so amazingly spicy that youre just sweating all through dinner, Roberts told People magazine.         
	The actress, who recently revealed that she is a practicing Hindu, also wore a sari for a scene in the film.         
	Eat Pray Love, which also stars James Franco and Oscar-winner Javier Bardem, releases in India next week.                                                                                                                                                          
